@Node "Conf"

        @{b}@{u}défault Configuration :@{ub}@{uu}

            ASC TO FAX Inverting               -> No
            IFF TO FAX Inverting               -> No
            FAX CONV   Inverting               -> No
            Bit order inverting when send      -> No
            Bit order inverting when convert   -> No
            LogFile when send                  -> Not Active
            Default Font                       -> Topaze.font
            Default font size                  -> 30
            Default Dest Number                -> None
            Header Lines use                   -> No
            Default Header Lines File          -> Header_Def
            FaxRecv Mode                       -> Not active

        @{b}@{u}Modifying startup configuration :@{ub}@{uu}

            All of elements can be configured to be in particular state at
            startup.
            Modification of ToolTypes in ECFAXEH icone is the way to make
            these changes.
            To do it, select ECFAXEH icone in ECFAX drawer, press the <AMIGA RIGHT>
            and <I> keys together. A window appear, if ECFAXEH has just been
            installed, ToolTypes are Default configured.
            Make the change that you want and clik on save gadget, now when
            you start ECFAXEH the config is loaded.



        @{b}@{u}ToolTypes List & possible values :@{ub}@{uu}

            IASC = Yes / No  -> ASC TO FAX Inverting.
            IIFF = Yes / No  -> IFF TO FAX Inverting.
            IFAX = Yes / No  -> FAX CONV   Inverting.
            BOS  = Yes / No  -> Bit order inverting when send.
            BOC  = Yes / No  -> Bit order inverting when convert.

            HEAD = Yes / NO  -> Header lines use.

            FONT = xyz.font  -> Default font name to use.
            FONTSIZE = 30    -> Default size font to use.
                                (value between 30 and 100)

            DEFDEST = xxxx.. -> Default Dest number to use.
                                (All of chars used in Dest field are
                                autorized)

            LOG = Yes / No   -> Log file when send

            HeadFile = xyz...-> Default Name and path of Header line file.


            Key = xyz...     -> Register Keycode given when you register your
                                version.
                                When this code is provided, the register
                                windows does not appear.

            FAXRECV = Yes/No -> FaxRecv mode at startup.


        @{b}@{u}To be noticed :@{ub}@{uu}

            When a ToolTypes is not present, default value will be used.


            All of these ToolType are ReWriten by @{"CFG" Link "UKFCT1.OVL/cfg"} gadget
            to reflect actual configuration of programm.





